{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WrxWHjRHztuH9Ce1oErqjA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01NYqC4XMMbofWN5f4vwviCx","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n demo create configmap config-audit --from-literal=findings.txt=\"$(cat <<'FINDINGS'\nINGRESS-NGINX COMPLIANCE AUDIT — 2026-06-24\n============================================\nCluster: kind (local), ingress-nginx v1.14.1, controller: ingress-nginx-controller\n\n=== FINDING 1 [HIGH] — Rate-limit burst value of 0 caused repeated nginx reload failures ===\nIngress: demo/rate-api\nAnnotations: limit-rps=1, limit-burst-multiplier=1\nEffect: nginx computes burst = (rps * multiplier) - 1 = 0, which is invalid.\nEvidence (logs): repeated '[emerg] invalid burst value \"burst=0\"' from 04:23:15 to 04:23:46;\ncontroller retried reload 3+ times before configuration was corrected.\nThe rate limit is now active but returns HTTP 503 (not RFC-standard 429) for throttled requests.\nFix: set limit-burst-multiplier >= 2 (burst = rps * multiplier - 1 must be >= 1), and add\nnginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-status-code: \"429\" for RFC 6585 compliance.\n\n=== FINDING 2 [HIGH] — No TLS configured on any Ingress ===\nIngresses: demo-app, rate-api, rate-health, canary-stable, canary-canary, canary-alt\nAll Ingress resources expose services over plain HTTP with no TLS termination configured.\nNo ssl-redirect or force-ssl-redirect annotations present. The controller ConfigMap also\nhas no global ssl-redirect setting. All traffic traverses the cluster unencrypted.\nFix: add TLS secret references to each Ingress spec.tls block and set\nnginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/force-ssl-redirect: \"true\".\n\n=== FINDING 3 [MEDIUM] — Orphaned canary Ingress silently drops traffic ===\nIngress: demo/canary-alt (label benchmark.decoy=true)\ncanary-alt declares nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary: \"true\" with host canary-alt.example.com,\nbut no primary (non-canary) Ingress exists for that hostname.\nEvidence (logs): repeated 'cannot merge alternative backend demo-stable-echo-80 into hostname\ncanary-alt.example.com that does not exist' — backend is silently dropped on every reconcile.\nThis decoy resource causes continuous controller log spam and the canary backend is unreachable.\nFix: either add a matching primary Ingress for canary-alt.example.com or remove canary-alt.\n\n=== FINDING 4 [MEDIUM] — Health endpoint not rate-limited on the same host as the rate-limited API ===\nIngresses: demo/rate-api (limit-rps=1 on /api), demo/rate-health (no limit on /health)\nBoth Ingresses share the host rate.example.com. /health is completely unrestricted while /api\nis rate-limited, creating an inconsistent protection boundary on the same virtual host.\nEvidence (logs): /health returns 200 at high volume concurrently with /api 503s during the same\nburst test — confirming no rate limit is applied to /health.\nFix: apply matching rate-limit annotations to rate-health, or document the intentional exemption.\n\n=== FINDING 5 [MEDIUM] — Conflicting --watch-ingress-without-class flags ===\nDeployment: ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller\nThe last-applied-configuration contains --watch-ingress-without-class=true, but the live pod\nspec also carries --watch-ingress-without-class=false added in a later patch (revision 2).\nBoth flags coexist in the args list; the last flag wins (=false), but the stale =true entry\ncreates a misleading and auditably inconsistent configuration.\nFix: remove the stale --watch-ingress-without-class=true arg, keeping only =false.\n\n=== FINDING 6 [MEDIUM] — No resource limits on the controller container ===\nDeployment: ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller\nOnly resource requests are set (cpu: 100m, memory: 90Mi); no limits are defined.\nUnder traffic surge the controller can consume unbounded CPU and memory, causing node pressure\nand evictions that affect unrelated workloads.\nFix: add resource limits commensurate with observed usage.\n\n=== FINDING 7 [LOW] — terminationGracePeriodSeconds set to 0 ===\nDeployment: ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller\nA grace period of 0 means the pod is SIGKILLed immediately during rolling updates or eviction,\nbypassing the /wait-shutdown preStop hook entirely. In-flight requests are dropped abruptly.\nFix: set terminationGracePeriodSeconds >= 30 to allow the preStop hook to drain connections.\n\n=== FINDING 8 [LOW] — readOnlyRootFilesystem: false ===\nContainer: controller in ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller\nThe container filesystem is writable. While the seccompProfile (RuntimeDefault) and dropped\ncapabilities reduce the blast radius, a read-only root filesystem is a defense-in-depth best\npractice that prevents runtime filesystem tampering.\nFix: set readOnlyRootFilesystem: true and mount writable tmpfs volumes for /tmp and any other\npaths nginx requires to write at runtime.\n\n=== FINDING 9 [LOW] — Single replica; no PodDisruptionBudget ===\nDeployment: ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller (replicas: 1, maxUnavailable: 1)\nThe controller has no redundancy. A rolling update, node drain, or pod eviction results in a\ncomplete ingress outage. No PodDisruptionBudget is configured to gate voluntary disruptions.\nFix: scale to >= 2 replicas and add a PodDisruptionBudget with minAvailable: 1.\n\n=== FINDING 10 [INFO] — Controller ConfigMap is empty; no global hardening applied ===\nConfigMap: ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller (data: null)\nNo global nginx settings are configured (e.g., ssl-protocols, ssl-ciphers, hsts, log-format,\nproxy-buffer-size, keep-alive). Default values are used for all parameters.\nFix: review and set security-relevant global defaults appropriate for the environment.\n\n=== SUMMARY ===\nHIGH   : 2 (rate-limit burst=0 reload failures; no TLS on any Ingress)\nMEDIUM : 4 (orphaned canary; inconsistent rate-limit coverage; conflicting flags; no resource limits)\nLOW    : 3 (grace period 0; writable root filesystem; single replica/no PDB)\nINFO   : 1 (empty ConfigMap)\n\nAudit performed read-only. No cluster resources were modified.\nFINDINGS\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap in demo namespace with findings"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":16384,"cache_read_input_tokens":34904,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":16384},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b9ed8422-5df3-47ad-9c97-66391fa536e4","uuid":"5f0013df-6832-4782-acc6-20f846dc0572","request_id":"req_011CcMTAL9Vdz3vz8AkDCuFq"}
